    <AbstractNarration>This planning project is designed to improve mathematics science and learning &lt;br/&gt;opportunities for Sitting Bull College students, "to each according to his/her needs". &lt;br/&gt;The planning process will identify the needs of four distinct groups of students. &lt;br/&gt;Group one: students whose career fields do not require extensive mathematics and &lt;br/&gt;science preparation. Group two: students entering science and engineering fields. &lt;br/&gt;Group three: students entering fields such as human services and business where &lt;br/&gt;mathematic curriculum can be taught to make use of quantitative methods in &lt;br/&gt;decision making. Group four: students entering the elementary and middle school&lt;br/&gt;teaching, and must be aware of North and South Dakota performance standards.</AbstractNarration>
